1
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,940
=About Love=

2
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 26=

3
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,510
Xi.

4
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,680
First stir the dye well.

5
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:48,000
Soak the cloth

6
00:01:48,310 --> 00:01:49,840
completely in it.

7
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,840
Stir in one direction.

8
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:54,590
Let the cotton absorb the dye fully.

9
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:57,000
It looks like this now.

10
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,120
Once you take it out and it oxidizes.

11
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,870
It'll turn deep blue.

12
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,400
Hey, Xi.

13
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:06,640
Do you remember?

14
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:10,630
When you were little,
you went up the mountain with Mom

15
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,520
and picked Ban Lan Gen
to boil into dye.

16
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,870
The color we got was this deep blue.

17
00:02:15,030 --> 00:02:16,360
How could I forget?

18
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,520
I had a red dress when I was little.

19
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,430
I dyed it myself.

20
00:02:19,870 --> 00:02:22,750
That one was dyed with Heqing red clay.

21
00:02:23,190 --> 00:02:24,630
Crofton weed.

22
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:26,520
All year round,

23
00:02:26,910 --> 00:02:28,280
you can dye shades of yellow with it.

24
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:32,310
With walnut skins,
you get a brown-grey hue.

25
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:36,430
With mimeng flowers,
you get a soft green-blue.

26
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,560
As craftsmen,

27
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,840
you should be content.

28
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:43,800
The heavens

29
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:46,310
has given us so much.

30
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,120
What more could you complain about?

31
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,280
Dad.

32
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,120
Mm?

33
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:03,030
I saw a wedding photo

34
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,590
in my friend's store.

35
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:07,120
You were in it too.

36
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:13,750
And my friend said

37
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:16,800
you are the bride's father.

38
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,520
Mingming.

39
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,310
- Hey.
- Xi, you're here.

40
00:03:20,310 --> 00:03:21,470
- Tidying up alone?
- Mm.

41
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,590
- Need a hand?
- It's fine.

42
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,470
Almost done. That's it.

43
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,750
You really don't plan to continue?

44
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:30,940
Mm, I'm done.

45
00:03:32,230 --> 00:03:33,870
The landlord
keeps urging me to move out.

46
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,800
The nearby shops keep complaining.

47
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,000
Starting tomorrow,

48
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,560
this place will
have nothing to do with me.

49
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,470
Oh, I'll get the photo for you.

50
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:46,990
- Wait a second.
- Okay.

51
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:12,560
Found it.

52
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,280
Sorry, things are so messy.

53
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,840
Oh.

54
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,200
What's wrong?

55
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:21,350
Nothing.

56
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,600
This photo came out really well.

57
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:25,630
When was it taken?

58
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:27,680
About a month or two ago.

59
00:04:31,270 --> 00:04:33,510
Do you know the man in the middle?

60
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,600
He's... oh, the bride's father.

61
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,560
You know him?

62
00:04:44,210 --> 00:04:46,040
I remember
seeing it once when I was little.

63
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:49,680
You held that little girl in your arms.

64
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,190
And gave her a

65
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:54,000
music box exactly like mine.

66
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,000
So,

67
00:04:57,310 --> 00:04:59,040
that's why you broke your music box?

68
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:00,230
Mm.

69
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,560
That little girl

70
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,120
is your elder sister.

71
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:15,630
Xi.

72
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:20,950
There are some things

73
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,680
that you can now be told.

74
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,040
Do you know

75
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:28,430
how your mom and I

76
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,920
met?

77
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,270
I remembered you two said

78
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:35,680
you met right here.

79
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,800
You came here to
work in the countryside.

80
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,310
Before I

81
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,800
met your mom,

82
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:45,120
I had

83
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:48,240
a girlfriend
I was really close to in the city.

84
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:52,190
We were together for six or seven years.

85
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:55,430
We were supposed to get married.

86
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:58,430
But her father refused to agree.

87
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:01,070
There was nothing I could do.

88
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,190
So we broke up.

89
00:06:05,630 --> 00:06:07,510
I was in turmoil back then,

90
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,560
so I followed the unit's arrangement.

91
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,240
Came to the countryside for research.

92
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:15,510
At that time,

93
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:18,070
your mother was on vacation from school.

94
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:20,360
Back home,

95
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,310
she helped out at the dye workshop.

96
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,560
It wasn't love at first sight.

97
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:27,270
But after spending a few days together,

98
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,920
I really loved talking to you mom.

99
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,390
Loved hearing her laugh.

100
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:34,760
Soon,

101
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,800
we became

102
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,160
a couple.

103
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,310
Started dating.

104
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:43,630
After that,

105
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:47,070
I decided to find a job
in the countryside

106
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:48,600
and moved here.

107
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:51,390
But what I didn't expect,

108
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,480
right after I married your mother,

109
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,800
my ex reached out.

110
00:06:58,430 --> 00:07:00,310
By then, she had already had the baby.

111
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:03,270
I didn't find out
until after we broke up.

112
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,680
She never told me.

113
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,630
When your mother found out,

114
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,800
she was really hurt.

115
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,160
She had a fierce quarrel with me.

116
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:16,480
We almost got divorced.

117
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:21,630
But after calming down,

118
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,560
we accepted the truth.

119
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:27,560
After all,

120
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,630
the child was innocent.

121
00:07:31,430 --> 00:07:32,270
Later on,

122
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,120
I told my ex-girlfriend

123
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:37,070
the one I love now is your mother.

124
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:40,040
I would never go back to her again.

125
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:44,040
But the child was welcome
to return anytime.

126
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:47,950
Your mom and I were willing to take on

127
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,630
some of the parenting responsibilities.

128
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:53,240
Shortly after that,

129
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,600
your mother got pregnant with you too.

130
00:07:58,390 --> 00:08:01,120
We were afraid you were too young

131
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,800
to understand something like this.

132
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:06,800
And that it might hurt you.

133
00:08:09,310 --> 00:08:10,870
So we decided to keep it from you first.

134
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:13,120
Later,

135
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:16,600
the other woman got married
and started her own family.

136
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:19,670
And we

137
00:08:19,950 --> 00:08:21,310
gradually lost touch.

138
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:26,310
There was even less reason to tell you.

139
00:08:36,910 --> 00:08:37,750
Hey.

140
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,320
Time's almost up.

141
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:40,750
Hey.

142
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,440
Let me take a look.

143
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,280
Let's see.

144
00:08:43,550 --> 00:08:44,390
Whoa.

145
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:46,750
Not bad.

146
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:48,560
It changed color.

147
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,000
Nice.

148
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:52,790
Looks nice.

149
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,360
Everything's ready now.

150
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,200
Just waiting for it to oxidize.

151
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,150
Here's your coffee.

152
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:34,510
Thank you.

153
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:39,870
Your coffee.

154
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,240
Hey, wait a second.

155
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:45,320
Does this look like you?

156
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,440
This one.

157
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,030
Hey, doesn't it?

158
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,150
It's already the seventh day.

159
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:52,990
Mm.

160
00:09:53,870 --> 00:09:54,910
Why are they two

161
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,390
competing like this?

162
00:09:56,390 --> 00:09:57,240
Bad call.

163
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:58,550
I talked too much. My bad.

164
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:01,000
Suddenly told them
Xiaoxi would contact me.

165
00:10:01,020 --> 00:10:01,870
Now

166
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:03,870
they're competing.
Giving me a hard time.

167
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,480
What if Li Xiaoxi

168
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,670
never contacts us?

169
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:08,600
Just keep doing what we're doing.

170
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,080
Treat them like two guardian gods

171
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,630
to ward off bad luck.

172
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,320
Go ahead.

173
00:10:19,310 --> 00:10:25,400
♪I'm just waiting♪

174
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:27,350
(To: Xiaoxi)
(Xiaoxi,)

175
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:28,750
(you'll never guess)

176
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:31,120
(I've learned to do coffee latte art.)

177
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,560
(Qin taught me.)

178
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,750
(They say you're even better at it.)

179
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,160
(When you return,)

180
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:37,670
(will you show me yourself?)

181
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:41,510
(Yingtao doesn't come to the store
much anymore)

182
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,720
(She said
she's leaving everything to me.)

183
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:47,030
(But as an amateur,
I can only keep the business going.)

184
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,280
(Xiaoxi,)

185
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:49,550
(come back soon.)

186
00:10:49,810 --> 00:10:50,960
(The coffee store needs you.)

187
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:59,100
♪Waiting for the right time♪

188
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:01,000
(My mother
came back from overseas today.)

189
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,510
(She's eager to see you.)

190
00:11:03,870 --> 00:11:06,120
(I told her
you were working abroad recently.)

191
00:11:06,870 --> 00:11:07,870
(She was a bit disappointed.)

192
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:09,910
(But when she heard Yingtao
and the others talk about you)

193
00:11:09,910 --> 00:11:10,840
(she got happy again.)

194
00:11:11,510 --> 00:11:13,550
(She's waiting to meet you soon.)

195
00:11:14,870 --> 00:11:17,080
(She even asked someone
to pick some auspicious dates.)

196
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:19,550
(Said they're perfect
for getting married)

197
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:22,030
(But I don't think it'll work this year)

198
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,360
(Next year should be good)

199
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:25,440
(Chinese style or Western style.)

200
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:27,600
(Here or abroad.)

201
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,200
(Whatever you decide,
I'll go along with it.)

202
00:11:29,870 --> 00:11:30,870
(As long as you're willing.)

203
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:32,820
(Send)

204
00:11:33,070 --> 00:11:40,420
♪I don't really mind to
wait till I'm older♪

205
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:42,910
(It's been nearly a month in a blink.)

206
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:45,080
(No idea where you are right now.)

207
00:11:45,870 --> 00:11:46,790
(Or what you're doing?)

208
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,440
(Have you thought of me?)

209
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:53,010
♪Waiting for the right time♪

210
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,840
(I drank too much yesterday.)

211
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,390
(It was at a gathering
with Xiu and the others.)

212
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,320
(You'd never guess)

213
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,750
(Luanluan was spotted
by a famous director)

214
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:02,870
(He offered her the lead role.)

215
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,320
(Sen joked that)

216
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:07,200
(if Xiu hadn't held her back,)

217
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:09,670
(Luanluan might've been
a star long ago.)

218
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:12,510
(You should have seen
how bad Xiu's face looked)

219
00:12:12,790 --> 00:12:14,630
(But he got over it later.)

220
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,480
(Said if he'd known earlier,)

221
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,720
(he'd have asked Luanluan
for more autographs.)

222
00:12:19,550 --> 00:12:20,390
(I think)

223
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,870
(Even their grudges can be resolved)

224
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:24,920
(Then what about us?)

225
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,630
(These days I keep thinking back.)

226
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:30,270
(Those days I refused to
communicate with you)

227
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:32,840
(That cold treatment)

228
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:34,080
(It was really too much)

229
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:35,960
(Can you forgive me?)

230
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,000
(We probably have about
20,000 days left in our lives.)

231
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,550
(Every day I don't see you is a regret)

232
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,120
(Come back.)

233
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,080
(I really miss you.)

234
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:47,990
Bei.

235
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,790
Coffee for table three, thank you.

236
00:12:50,790 --> 00:12:51,630
Okay.

237
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:53,570
- Okay. This way.
- Let me do it.

238
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:57,840
I think a hundred
macaron-colored balloons

239
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,630
should be enough, right?

240
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:01,200
Start with a hundred.
Add more if needed.

241
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:02,870
Okay. And for the wedding accompaniment,

242
00:13:02,870 --> 00:13:04,030
we can ask Xiu to play.

243
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,870
That way we can save some money.

244
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:06,720
The effect will be good.

245
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,570
Okay.

246
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:08,720
You're good at arranging things.

247
00:13:09,150 --> 00:13:11,000
What? Can't let you sing one song?

248
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,040
Huh?

249
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,240
Talking about money hurts feelings.

250
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:15,870
Not gonna eat it? I'll take it.

251
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:16,710
Hey.

252
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,030
My wife hasn't eaten yet.

253
00:13:18,210 --> 00:13:19,200
What kind of waiter are you?

254
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:20,750
No sense of observation at all.

255
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,440
Here, babe, take a bite.

256
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,080
I'm wearing a wedding dress.
I'm not eating.

257
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:26,390
I'm wearing a suit too.

258
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:27,560
I'm not eating either.

259
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:28,800
Take it away.

260
00:13:29,030 --> 00:13:29,870
Here.

261
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,630
Enough.

262
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:33,480
Go be lovey-dovey at home.

263
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,030
Can't you see there are people here?

264
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,320
To be honest,

265
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:37,870
when I was single,

266
00:13:37,870 --> 00:13:39,600
you kept shoving your love in my face.

267
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,790
Especially you, Gong.

268
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:42,030
Now justice has been served.

269
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,390
I'm the first one to settle down.

270
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:45,510
It just goes to show

271
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,480
there are no shortcuts to love.

272
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,200
You should give sincerely and steadily.

273
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,080
I really admire myself.

274
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,440
All these years,

275
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,320
I haven't been influenced

276
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,870
by all your bad habits.

277
00:13:56,030 --> 00:13:57,630
I'm totally clean in the mess.

278
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:58,790
I stay graceful, not showy.

279
00:13:58,790 --> 00:14:00,480
Wow, so impressive.

280
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:02,200
Bei Qiyuan.

281
00:14:03,870 --> 00:14:04,870
He says you're showy.

282
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,320
I'm not as showy as you.

283
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,160
Gong Yuanqian.

284
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,360
I won't argue with you.

285
00:14:10,630 --> 00:14:12,440
When Xiaoxi returns,she'll know

286
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,910
who truly loves her the most.

287
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,270
Don't cry when that time comes.

288
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,440
Keep living in your little fantasy.

289
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,200
Take care of yourself.

290
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:21,910
I'll handle things here.

291
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,440
Mm, goodbye.

292
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:26,990
Whose call was that?

293
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:27,910
Li Xiaoxi.

294
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:28,750
I spoke to her.

295
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:31,120
You talk to her? I'll talk to her.

296
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,320
Go on.

297
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:37,910
Well, you two...

298
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,600
Have been at it for a whole month.

299
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,670
Is it ever going to end?

300
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:41,960
If I were Li Xiaoxi,

301
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,390
I'd pick neither if I was annoyed.

302
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:44,360
In this world,

303
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,510
there are plenty of other guys.

304
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,240
That's not entirely true.

305
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,910
Gong is a bit of a player.

306
00:14:48,910 --> 00:14:50,870
But a reformed playboy is priceless.

307
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:52,960
How many girls' hearts have you broken?

308
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,030
What if, just what if.

309
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,240
What if Li Xiaoxi is

310
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,630
the Zixia Fairy
who can draw your sword?

311
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:58,510
The Zixia Fairy.

312
00:14:58,510 --> 00:15:00,390
If you miss that chance,
let's be monk together.

313
00:15:02,870 --> 00:15:04,510
Since you got divorced,

314
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,360
this is the smartest thing you've said.

315
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,550
Who says Bei can't be a monk?

316
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,240
Love isn't charity.

317
00:15:10,390 --> 00:15:11,600
Giving to whoever needs it.

318
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,080
Li Xiaoxi is so sad right now.

319
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:14,920
You know what that means?

320
00:15:14,930 --> 00:15:16,440
It means she still loves Bei.

321
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:20,360
Love and hate are
two sides of the same coin.

322
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:21,790
At least you need to
have the coin first.

323
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,600
How do you know there's no coin

324
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:24,960
between me and Xiaoxi?

325
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:26,000
Fair point.

326
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,440
Emotional foundation is crucial.

327
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,680
You can't force it.

328
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:30,600
Do you have any independent judgment?

329
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,360
You're such a flip-flopper.

330
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:33,840
He's not wrong.

331
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,320
Bei.

332
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:38,160
Mm.

333
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,600
Do you love Li Xiaoxi?

334
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:41,160
Of course I do.

335
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,870
Then what are you waiting for?

336
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:44,360
What era is it now?

337
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,960
If you truly want to find someone,

338
00:15:46,550 --> 00:15:47,630
there's always a way.

339
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,240
Hey, buddy, buddy.

340
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:06,960
Help me track a phone number.

341
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,440
It's for rescue, to save...

342
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:10,230
What?

343
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:12,000
It's illegal?

344
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:31,600
You've been back nearly a month now.

345
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,120
Got any plans?

346
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,870
What? Are you tired of me?

347
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,870
Tired of you?

348
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,390
I wish you'd stay at home.

349
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:40,390
Never leave.

350
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:41,910
Stay as long as you want.

351
00:16:48,060 --> 00:16:50,540
(Bei)

352
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,280
Alright.

353
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:54,480
I caught a fish
in the field this morning.

354
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:55,910
Best served as a fresh stew.

355
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,750
And these bamboo shoots,
perfect for braising meat.

356
00:16:58,750 --> 00:16:59,590
Okay.

357
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,910
I'll go next door to borrow some ginger.

358
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:07,920
I'll be back in a moment.

359
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:10,680
Where are you getting ginger from?

360
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,310
Didn't he head out?

361
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,110
Hello?

362
00:17:21,110 --> 00:17:22,000
Hello, uncle.

363
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:23,510
It's me, Bei.

364
00:17:23,990 --> 00:17:24,830
No, no, you...

365
00:17:24,830 --> 00:17:26,510
Please, don't hang up yet.

366
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,440
I promise I won't ask about Xiaoxi.

367
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,200
Yes, I just want to

368
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:33,830
chat casually with you.

369
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:35,240
Okay.

370
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:37,640
Then let's just have a casual chat.

371
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:38,880
Well, uncle,

372
00:17:39,070 --> 00:17:40,720
I heard it's travel season lately.

373
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:42,590
Business at your homestay

374
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:44,270
must be really good, right?

375
00:17:44,590 --> 00:17:45,430
Plenty of visitors,

376
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,110
right?

377
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:48,400
Indeed.

378
00:17:49,350 --> 00:17:50,510
But I

379
00:17:50,510 --> 00:17:52,510
don't like doing promotions.

380
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,510
Everyone who comes are repeat customers.

381
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:57,110
Old friends for years.

382
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:58,840
Ah.

383
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,590
With so many guests,

384
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,640
does aunt have to

385
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,000
cook more dishes every day?

386
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,640
Yes, yes.

387
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,590
Really busy.

388
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,070
Just now I went to the river to catch

389
00:18:09,270 --> 00:18:11,270
a fresh fish for a female guest.

390
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,350
Let her taste
the flavor of her childhood.

391
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:17,790
You can't get this in the city.

392
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:20,910
Well…

393
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:23,310
Uncle, I... I…

394
00:18:23,550 --> 00:18:25,000
Last time I saw you

395
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,590
really liked carving.

396
00:18:27,110 --> 00:18:29,030
I specially bought two

397
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:31,640
albums of famous carvers.

398
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:32,830
So, give me your address?

399
00:18:32,830 --> 00:18:33,720
I'll send them to you.

400
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,830
I'm at Fuxi Inn.

401
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:38,110
What?

402
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:39,400
Fuxi Inn.

403
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,880
I also have a line here.

404
00:18:42,030 --> 00:18:44,720
"White egrets fly over Xisai Mountain.

405
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,310
Peach blossoms flow,
mandarin fish fatten."

406
00:18:47,980 --> 00:18:48,830
No, this...

407
00:18:48,830 --> 00:18:50,030
Wh... what does it mean?

408
00:18:50,030 --> 00:18:51,920
Hey, Bei.

409
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,720
Why are you so simple-minded?

410
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,480
Xisai Mountain.

411
00:18:58,830 --> 00:19:00,590
I get it. Thank you, uncle, thank you.

412
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,110
Well...

413
00:19:02,110 --> 00:19:03,830
I'll definitely
sent those albums to you.

414
00:19:04,020 --> 00:19:04,880
Don't worry.

415
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:05,830
Ah, don't worry.

416
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,040
Yeah.

417
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:12,720
Who are you calling?

418
00:19:15,110 --> 00:19:16,000
None of your business.

419
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:17,350
Where are you going?

420
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:18,760
The bathroom.

421
00:19:22,110 --> 00:19:22,950
What are you doing?

422
00:19:23,190 --> 00:19:24,030
Using the bathroom.

423
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:24,880
Then go. Here.

424
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:25,720
You go.

425
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:26,800
I'm not going.

426
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,310
Why you gotta follow me?

427
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:31,440
I need to go too.

428
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:33,950
Wait, wait.

429
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,350
So inhumane.

430
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:44,070
- Hey, buddy.
- Huh?

431
00:19:44,070 --> 00:19:45,000
Come here.

432
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,030
Can you give me a hand?

433
00:19:46,030 --> 00:19:46,870
Mm.

434
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:55,950
Hello, who's speaking?

435
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,680
Is this Mr. Gong?

436
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,160
It's me. What's up?

437
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,920
I contacted your editor before.

438
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:03,310
I really admire your work.

439
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,200
I'd like to adapt it into a TV drama.

440
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,440
Adapt my work

441
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:09,880
into a TV drama?

442
00:20:10,230 --> 00:20:11,160
Yes.

443
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:13,240
Want to talk to you about copyright.

444
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,680
Oh.

445
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,240
Where are you now?

446
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:19,350
Here's the thing.

447
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:20,640
I'm at the airport.

448
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,160
I only have an hour.

449
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:23,830
If you're interested,

450
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:25,240
we can meet and talk.

451
00:20:26,790 --> 00:20:28,240
And the price...

452
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,750
The price is not an issue.

453
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:33,310
Oh, alright.

454
00:20:33,310 --> 00:20:34,190
Then I…

455
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:35,590
Please don't leave just yet.

456
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:36,790
I'll come find you now.

457
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,000
That's it?

458
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:03,000
Do I look that easy to fool?

459
00:21:35,070 --> 00:21:36,680
You're like a lingering ghost.

460
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:37,680
What exactly do you want?

461
00:21:37,830 --> 00:21:39,960
Only those with guilt fear ghosts.

462
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,160
Didn't you meet the director?

463
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:47,350
Keep pretending.

464
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:49,270
Go on.

465
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,590
When I did this kind of stuff,

466
00:21:51,590 --> 00:21:53,310
you were still making mud dolls.

467
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:54,800
Just confess.

468
00:21:55,590 --> 00:21:56,430
Where are you going?

469
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:57,790
It's none of your business.

470
00:21:57,790 --> 00:21:59,510
Can't I go travel? Just relax.

471
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:00,590
Sure.

472
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:02,350
Of course you can.

473
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:05,350
What a coincidence, I'm traveling too.

474
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,240
I need to relax too.

475
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:09,070
Wherever you go, I'll go.

476
00:22:09,270 --> 00:22:10,720
Wherever you get off, I'll get off.

477
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,070
I'm sticking with you.

478
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:13,800
Suit yourself.

479
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:24,150
Eh.

480
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:25,350
Sit in the back.

481
00:22:25,350 --> 00:22:28,180
(Taxi)

482
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,510
Sit in the front and pay.

483
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:35,560
Drive!

484
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:39,070
Stop! Stop the car!

485
00:22:40,550 --> 00:22:41,790
Bei Qiyuan!

486
00:22:42,030 --> 00:22:44,350
You have no manners!

487
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,350
(Waiting Room)
Hello, I'd like a ticket to...

488
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:48,680
Xisai Mountain, please.

489
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:50,110
Please show your ID first.

490
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:51,480
Ah, alright.

491
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:57,880
Don't look for it,
it's right here with me.

492
00:23:00,030 --> 00:23:01,350
Surprised, huh?

493
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:05,510
I knew you'd pull this trick
when getting off the train.

494
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:10,070
What other tricks do you have?

495
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:11,550
Bring them on.

496
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:15,800
Excuse me.

497
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:16,960
Two tickets.

498
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:17,800
Okay.

499
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,510
You pay for it.

500
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:31,380
(Passenger Vehicle Temporary
Pick-up Point)

501
00:23:36,510 --> 00:23:37,350
You know what.

502
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:38,550
Following me is useless.

503
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:39,510
No idea either.

504
00:23:41,310 --> 00:23:42,240
Cut the crap.

505
00:23:42,590 --> 00:23:43,680
We're already here.

506
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,040
Let's go.

507
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:53,940
(Passenger Vehicle Temporary
Pick-up Point)

508
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:02,030
Why rush like that? Wait for me!

509
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,160
You…

510
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,590
What's the hurry with you?

511
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,960
We've been walking for hours.

512
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,240
Aren't you tired?

513
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,830
Such beautiful scenery here.

514
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:18,550
Why not stop and rest?

515
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,200
Rest if you want.

516
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:23,070
I never asked you to follow me.

517
00:24:24,550 --> 00:24:25,750
- You...
- Hey.

518
00:24:25,750 --> 00:24:27,270
Today, I'm set on keeping up with you.

519
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,270
What are you doing?

520
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:38,440
Enjoy life.

521
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,110
This place…

522
00:25:06,110 --> 00:25:07,960
Feels like we've been here before.

523
00:25:09,310 --> 00:25:10,310
It's this tree.

524
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,080
Care for a drink?

525
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:23,640
That jerk is playing dirty again.

526
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:31,350
Where are my shoes?

527
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:47,480
Water!

528
00:25:48,110 --> 00:25:49,830
Hurry! Give me some water!

529
00:25:53,030 --> 00:25:53,870
Hey.

530
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:55,040
Five yuan.

531
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,550
Mm.

532
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:04,480
Alright, alright.

533
00:26:06,750 --> 00:26:07,960
Here, mom.

534
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:08,880
Mm, put it here.

535
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,750
Mm, I've cleaned it for you.

536
00:26:11,890 --> 00:26:12,730
Is that alright?

537
00:26:12,750 --> 00:26:13,640
Yeah.

538
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,480
Did you weave this?

539
00:26:16,110 --> 00:26:17,160
Wow.

540
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,920
You've been happier these past two days.

541
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:21,670
- Mm-hmm.
- Much better now?

542
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:22,720
Much better.

543
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:25,000
You were just like this
when you were little.

544
00:26:25,310 --> 00:26:27,200
Moody one moment, cheerful the next.

545
00:26:27,640 --> 00:26:29,240
No one knows who you take after.

546
00:26:31,830 --> 00:26:32,830
I look so good.

547
00:26:32,830 --> 00:26:34,310
Of course, I take after you.

548
00:26:34,830 --> 00:26:36,110
Couldn't be my father.

549
00:26:36,110 --> 00:26:37,030
His nose is so big.

550
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:38,310
Your temper is like your dad's.

551
00:26:39,270 --> 00:26:40,790
When your father first came here,

552
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:43,200
he seemed gloomy all day.

553
00:26:44,070 --> 00:26:45,830
Just buried himself in work.

554
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:50,160
Like tie-Dye and fishing.

555
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,640
He learned them all from scratch.

556
00:26:53,240 --> 00:26:55,440
Especially that wood carving.

557
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:57,350
Neither your grandpa nor I
could learn it.

558
00:26:57,830 --> 00:26:58,830
He learned it right away.

559
00:26:58,960 --> 00:26:59,920
Really?

560
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:00,830
My father's amazing.

561
00:27:00,830 --> 00:27:01,670
Yeah.

562
00:27:03,350 --> 00:27:04,510
Just like when you were a kid,

563
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:06,110
you loved drawing those animals.

564
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:08,400
You think those wood carvings

565
00:27:08,590 --> 00:27:09,920
your dad sent you were so ugly?

566
00:27:10,070 --> 00:27:12,350
He drew them all based on

567
00:27:12,350 --> 00:27:13,400
your childhood drawings.

568
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:14,830
He sent them to you,
but you ignored him.

569
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,080
Eh.

570
00:27:16,350 --> 00:27:17,720
They were my drawings?

571
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:21,000
No wonder they looked like that.

572
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,550
- How strange.
- Otherwise they'd be less ugly.

573
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,240
Handsome guy.

574
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:27,830
Here for travel? Having fun?

575
00:27:28,510 --> 00:27:30,590
Our mountains and rivers
are beautiful here.

576
00:27:31,240 --> 00:27:32,680
Lots to do.

577
00:27:35,270 --> 00:27:36,240
Okay.

578
00:27:45,550 --> 00:27:47,000
Sir, can I have a piece of bread?

579
00:27:47,350 --> 00:27:48,190
Sure.

580
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:52,830
Excuse me, make way.

581
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,040
Step aside.

582
00:27:57,510 --> 00:27:59,880
See you again, Mr. Bei.

583
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:10,640
What is that?

584
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:12,310
Mosquito repellent.

585
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,320
Eh.

586
00:28:21,310 --> 00:28:22,160
Can we make a deal?

587
00:28:23,350 --> 00:28:24,190
What deal?

588
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:26,190
Let's call a truce.

589
00:28:26,590 --> 00:28:27,590
We're already here.

590
00:28:28,030 --> 00:28:29,550
Just tell me where Xiaoxi is.

591
00:28:29,550 --> 00:28:30,390
That's all.

592
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,350
Maybe with my smarts,

593
00:28:32,790 --> 00:28:33,920
I can find her.

594
00:28:34,590 --> 00:28:35,920
You guard me like I'm some thief.

595
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:37,350
Is that necessary?

596
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:38,480
Of course it is.

597
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:39,510
I found the clue.

598
00:28:39,510 --> 00:28:40,590
Why should I share it with you?

599
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:44,030
Scared?

600
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:45,520
Scared of what?

601
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,590
Scared I'll find Xiaoxi first.

602
00:28:47,590 --> 00:28:48,720
And she'll accept me.

603
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:49,680
Leaving you with nothing.

604
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:51,350
You're really overthinking it.

605
00:28:53,530 --> 00:28:54,590
Aren't you choking on that?

606
00:29:01,340 --> 00:29:04,820
(Fuxi Inn)

607
00:29:05,100 --> 00:29:05,960
Wait, that's my phone.

608
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:07,000
Why are you taking my phone?

609
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,310
Saw it already.

610
00:29:10,070 --> 00:29:11,640
- Sir.
- Eh?

611
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:12,880
How do I get to Fuxi Inn?

612
00:29:13,070 --> 00:29:14,830
Everyone from the city goes there.

613
00:29:15,070 --> 00:29:16,880
Look, just climb over that mountain.

614
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:17,720
And you'll be there.

615
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,020
- Mom.
- Mm?

616
00:29:25,110 --> 00:29:26,200
When dad told you

617
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,750
about his affair,

618
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,880
were you really sad?

619
00:29:31,750 --> 00:29:33,160
How did you forgive him?

620
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,080
Just endure.

621
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:37,640
Endure it.

622
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:39,510
Saying "endure"

623
00:29:39,830 --> 00:29:41,440
makes it sound bad.

624
00:29:42,510 --> 00:29:43,680
Actually,

625
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:45,000
time

626
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:49,550
can heal many wounds.

627
00:29:50,510 --> 00:29:51,640
Back then I thought

628
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,160
if I got hurt,

629
00:29:53,310 --> 00:29:54,720
I'd run to your grandmother's place,

630
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,040
and hide away.

631
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,550
Would my grandmother know about this?

632
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:02,720
Yeah.

633
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:16,550
I think

634
00:30:17,350 --> 00:30:18,790
I'm going to die here today.

635
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:22,110
If I die later,

636
00:30:23,830 --> 00:30:25,640
my old father will be in your care.

637
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:27,750
Keep an eye on him.

638
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:30,030
Don't let him drink.

639
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:31,550
Die if you want.

640
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:33,480
Take care of your own dad.

641
00:30:33,750 --> 00:30:35,000
I still need to look after my Xiaoxi.

642
00:30:36,110 --> 00:30:36,950
Wait.

643
00:30:37,790 --> 00:30:38,630
You...

644
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:41,270
Why can't you just let it go?

645
00:30:42,030 --> 00:30:45,030
Heaven gave you a chance.

646
00:30:45,270 --> 00:30:46,960
But you didn't treasure it.

647
00:30:47,510 --> 00:30:50,160
You only regret it after losing her.

648
00:30:50,750 --> 00:30:53,640
Now your game is over.

649
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:55,350
Game over.

650
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,640
Next round is mine.

651
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:00,070
Are you even saying human words?

652
00:31:00,070 --> 00:31:00,910
Ah?

653
00:31:01,310 --> 00:31:03,270
Do you treat feelings like a game?

654
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:05,680
Bei Qiyuan,

655
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,640
I didn't think you'd be this shameless.

656
00:31:09,350 --> 00:31:12,350
When Xiaoxi was chasing you to make up,

657
00:31:12,350 --> 00:31:13,550
why didn't you say this?

658
00:31:13,550 --> 00:31:14,390
Huh?

659
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:16,550
You broke her heart completely.

660
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:19,550
Now you're
playing the affectionate prince, huh?

661
00:31:19,550 --> 00:31:20,720
You're just hypocritical.

662
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:22,640
You're the hypocritical one.

663
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:24,400
Who said

664
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,480
they wanted pure love?

665
00:31:27,030 --> 00:31:28,590
Didn't want a long-term relationship.

666
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:29,440
Huh?

667
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:30,510
So when it's your brother's wife,

668
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:31,590
suddenly everything's acceptable?

669
00:31:32,030 --> 00:31:34,680
Finally said it out loud.

670
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:36,480
Fine, I'll tell you.

671
00:31:37,030 --> 00:31:38,550
If Xiaoxi were with me,

672
00:31:38,550 --> 00:31:40,400
I'd never let her go back home in tears.

673
00:31:40,590 --> 00:31:42,200
I'll hold her dear and spoil her.

674
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:44,240
I'll make her happy every day.

675
00:31:44,790 --> 00:31:46,160
Li Xiaoxi loves me.

676
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,160
Even if she cries,

677
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:51,310
it would be tears of joy.

678
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:53,680
If she wanted to be with you,

679
00:31:54,230 --> 00:31:55,270
she would've done so long ago.

680
00:31:55,270 --> 00:31:56,240
Why wait until now?

681
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,280
Ah?

682
00:31:59,310 --> 00:32:00,310
Bei Qiyuan.

683
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,030
You're always so quiet.

684
00:32:02,030 --> 00:32:03,590
But now you've got plenty to say.

685
00:32:03,590 --> 00:32:04,440
What's wrong?

686
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:06,110
You're just too proud, too hard to read.

687
00:32:06,350 --> 00:32:07,240
No sense of romance!

688
00:32:07,550 --> 00:32:08,590
You're shameless.

689
00:32:08,830 --> 00:32:09,680
Hey.

690
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:12,000
You… you...

691
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,000
You were a telephone pole
in your past life!

692
00:32:21,510 --> 00:32:22,350
Hey.

693
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:23,760
Look over there.

694
00:32:26,790 --> 00:32:27,630
We're here.

695
00:32:58,310 --> 00:32:59,150
Xiaoxi.

696
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:00,560
Xiaoxi!

697
00:33:12,510 --> 00:33:13,440
Long time no see.

698
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:20,920
I'm sorry.

699
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,030
I won't run away anymore.

700
00:33:26,070 --> 00:33:27,240
Starting today,

701
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:29,960
I'll open up my heart.

702
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:36,070
I'll never be the way I was before.

703
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,030
This music box

704
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:54,110
was sent to me by the uncle.

705
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:57,790
I spent ages

706
00:33:58,310 --> 00:33:59,750
fixing it up, bit by bit.

707
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:03,760
I know

708
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,480
it's easy to
break something into pieces,

709
00:34:08,030 --> 00:34:09,510
but so hard to mend it back whole.

710
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:12,680
I admit that

711
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:15,800
I have character flaws.

712
00:34:17,510 --> 00:34:18,630
I tend to run from things,

713
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,880
to avoid facing so much in life.

714
00:34:24,190 --> 00:34:25,510
But these flaws of mine

715
00:34:26,670 --> 00:34:27,550
hurt you.

716
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:32,910
I'm sorry.

717
00:34:37,590 --> 00:34:38,550
I hope

718
00:34:39,590 --> 00:34:40,840
you can give me a chance

719
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:44,200
to let me

720
00:34:44,630 --> 00:34:46,030
fix those

721
00:34:47,070 --> 00:34:48,550
hurt feelings,

722
00:34:50,150 --> 00:34:51,480
bit by bit.

723
00:35:09,230 --> 00:35:10,070
Okay?

724
00:35:34,190 --> 00:35:35,670
Enough already.

725
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:37,670
Aren't you tired of this cliché?

726
00:35:44,190 --> 00:35:46,030
On the importance of a large bag.

727
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,440
Did you only put

728
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:50,070
the music box in your bag?

729
00:35:53,150 --> 00:35:53,990
Are you done?

730
00:35:54,230 --> 00:35:55,230
Step aside.

731
00:35:55,710 --> 00:35:56,710
My turn to talk.

732
00:35:58,270 --> 00:35:59,150
Go ahead.

733
00:35:59,150 --> 00:36:00,150
Say what you want.

734
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:03,880
Don't think it'll be unnecessary later.

735
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:08,640
Xiaoxi.

736
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,960
How can I speak with you standing there?

737
00:36:21,030 --> 00:36:22,670
You're actually shy?

738
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:25,840
When you were rambling

739
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:27,000
on and on here,

740
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:28,480
I held back all that time.

741
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,510
Your speech is over now.

742
00:36:30,510 --> 00:36:33,070
My turn. I'm the protagonist now!

743
00:36:33,630 --> 00:36:35,000
That's fair.

744
00:36:35,140 --> 00:36:36,920
Anyway, if you want to leave, you go.
I'm not leaving.

745
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:39,670
Why are you so shameless?

746
00:36:40,070 --> 00:36:41,510
Xiaoxi, wait a second.

747
00:36:41,610 --> 00:36:43,070
I need to
settle some old scores with him.

748
00:36:43,070 --> 00:36:44,030
Come here.

749
00:36:44,030 --> 00:36:45,030
Tell me, what are you up to?

750
00:36:45,030 --> 00:36:45,920
Come on, say it.

751
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:47,480
Which one's the son-in-law?

752
00:36:48,630 --> 00:36:49,480
That one, that one.

753
00:36:50,150 --> 00:36:51,920
The one as messy as a loach.

754
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:54,840
When he's cleaned up,

755
00:36:55,110 --> 00:36:56,400
he looks quite handsome.

756
00:36:57,030 --> 00:36:57,870
And that one?

757
00:36:58,440 --> 00:36:59,510
The slick-looking one.

758
00:37:00,110 --> 00:37:00,950
Don't know him.

759
00:37:01,190 --> 00:37:02,190
Looks like

760
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:05,280
both of them came here for Xiaoxi.

761
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:09,590
Two of them showed up at once.

762
00:37:12,190 --> 00:37:13,320
This is tricky.

763
00:37:14,110 --> 00:37:15,800
I'll count to three,
we both squat together.

764
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:16,760
See who's slower.

765
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:18,960
Are you out of your mind?

766
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:20,760
Do you hear yourself?

767
00:37:22,110 --> 00:37:23,710
- Let's change it.
- Come on.

768
00:37:23,710 --> 00:37:24,710
See that tree?

769
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:26,480
Let's race and see who gets there first.

770
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:28,280
Loser leaves right away, no stopping.

771
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:30,320
Wait, you want to race me?

772
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:31,160
Are you okay?

773
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:33,840
High‑waisted trousers.

774
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:36,550
Natural advantage.

775
00:37:37,190 --> 00:37:38,440
Can't I outrun you?

776
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:39,630
You get five seconds.

777
00:37:41,670 --> 00:37:43,320
You said it. No backing out later.

778
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:48,400
Ready.

779
00:37:54,030 --> 00:37:54,920
Xiaoxi, did you hear...

780
00:37:56,110 --> 00:37:56,950
Xiaoxi!

781
00:37:57,760 --> 00:37:58,600
Xiaoxi!

782
00:38:01,190 --> 00:38:02,320
Hurry, go save her!

783
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,320
Pull her back! I can't swim!

784
00:38:04,710 --> 00:38:06,190
I... I can't swim!

785
00:38:06,190 --> 00:38:07,070
You go down! You do it!

786
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:08,710
But I really can't swim!

787
00:38:09,110 --> 00:38:10,590
Hurry! I can't swim either!

788
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:12,320
I really can't swim!

789
00:38:12,670 --> 00:38:13,630
Xiaoxi!

790
00:38:13,630 --> 00:38:14,710
Save her now!

791
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,550
These kids are something else.

792
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,000
Let them play.

793
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:25,840
Xiaoxi grew up

794
00:38:26,510 --> 00:38:29,070
playing in this water.

795
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:31,150
Let's go.

796
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:32,440
Let's go.

797
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:33,280
Hey, let's go.

798
00:38:34,810 --> 00:38:38,620
♪Maybe withered flowers
still have fragrance♪

799
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:40,480
What are you staring at? Let's go.

800
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:43,280
Don't panic.

801
00:38:43,710 --> 00:38:46,690
♪Remember your young self♪

802
00:38:46,690 --> 00:38:49,330
♪Yearning for tomorrow and beyond♪

803
00:38:49,330 --> 00:38:52,550
♪Bravely waiting through
the night till dawn♪

804
00:38:52,670 --> 00:38:54,710
(Does perfect love exist?)

805
00:38:55,710 --> 00:38:57,550
(When I was little,
I often asked myself this.)

806
00:38:58,630 --> 00:38:59,480
(In the fairy tales,)

807
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:01,480
(love is described as supreme.)

808
00:39:02,110 --> 00:39:04,070
(The male lead
is always a perfect, rich)

809
00:39:04,280 --> 00:39:06,000
(and powerful hero)

810
00:39:07,070 --> 00:39:09,190
(When we grow up and face life,
we realize)

811
00:39:09,550 --> 00:39:11,920
(people have so many desires.)

812
00:39:12,960 --> 00:39:14,030
(How can there be)

813
00:39:14,030 --> 00:39:15,820
(such simple love stories?)

814
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:19,480
(Each person is a complex being.)

815
00:39:19,920 --> 00:39:22,150
(It's impossible to be
wholly owned by another.)

816
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,320
(In the game of love,)

817
00:39:25,480 --> 00:39:26,760
(some people yearn for)

818
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:28,230
(lifelong devotion)

819
00:39:29,190 --> 00:39:31,800
(and believe love is an eternal vow.)

820
00:39:33,190 --> 00:39:34,920
(Some people
look forward to the ambiguity)

821
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:36,480
(and passion brought by hormones.)

822
00:39:37,190 --> 00:39:40,070
(Believing true love
should not be bound by morals.)

823
00:39:41,110 --> 00:39:43,710
(Some people
get hurt after giving their all.)

824
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:45,190
(Then they never love again.)

825
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:49,320
(We all believe in eternal love.)

826
00:39:50,070 --> 00:39:52,000
(Yet we've all been hurt.)

827
00:39:53,590 --> 00:39:54,920
(We are in unbearable pain.)

828
00:39:55,190 --> 00:39:56,190
(Wash our face with tears.)

829
00:39:57,710 --> 00:40:00,510
(The beauty once held
can vanish in a blink.)

830
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:02,280
(Giving without reservation)

831
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:04,320
(can be ignored and taken for granted.)

832
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:06,720
♪Don't forget the dreams
of your childhood♪

833
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:08,840
(The one you loved with all your soul)

834
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:11,000
(can become unrecognizable.)

835
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:15,920
(We stumble along the way.)

836
00:40:16,070 --> 00:40:17,400
(Falling and getting bruised.)

837
00:40:17,840 --> 00:40:18,960
(We wait persistently.)

838
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:20,440
(Yet may never find an ending.)

839
00:40:21,550 --> 00:40:24,190
(Those profound hurts are real.)

840
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,630
(We feel tangled and guilty.)

841
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:30,110
(Always wondering what's wrong with us.)

842
00:40:32,150 --> 00:40:33,840
(So we begin to wonder)

843
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:36,000
(if love really is)

844
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,920
(that terrible poison apple)

845
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:39,510
(used to torture people?)

846
00:40:41,090 --> 00:40:43,180
♪Chase after the setting sun♪

847
00:40:44,230 --> 00:40:45,510
(Do not doubt yourself.)

848
00:40:46,230 --> 00:40:47,710
(You should care about yourself.)

849
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:49,960
(Believe that you're worthy of love.)

850
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,230
(Love is an)

851
00:40:52,510 --> 00:40:53,920
(unexplainable fate.)

852
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:56,670
(Cherish everything when you have it.)

853
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:59,360
(Let go with grace when love fades.)

854
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:02,960
(How many vows end up as)

855
00:41:03,150 --> 00:41:05,190
(screams and breakups?)

856
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:07,400
(Life still goes on)

857
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:09,110
(in the vastness of ordinary days.)

858
00:41:09,810 --> 00:41:11,850
♪Break free from the long night♪

859
00:41:11,880 --> 00:41:12,760
(As time passes,)

860
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:14,710
(the hatred we felt,)

861
00:41:15,070 --> 00:41:15,960
(and the disappointment)

862
00:41:16,510 --> 00:41:18,480
(will all fade with time.)

863
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:23,030
Your return
to accept the award this time

864
00:41:23,030 --> 00:41:24,710
has attracted many media attention.

865
00:41:24,710 --> 00:41:26,320
Will you consider staying abroad?

866
00:41:26,510 --> 00:41:27,400
Of course not.

867
00:41:27,670 --> 00:41:28,630
This is my home.

868
00:41:29,070 --> 00:41:31,190
Once I finish my studies, I'll come back

869
00:41:31,480 --> 00:41:32,670
and build my own brand.

870
00:41:32,920 --> 00:41:33,760
The award speech said

871
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:35,110
your work reveals

872
00:41:35,110 --> 00:41:36,880
a whole new and opened-up world.

873
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:38,150
What's your take on that?

874
00:41:39,510 --> 00:41:41,320
No one grows up in an instant.

875
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,590
Every day we discover

876
00:41:43,590 --> 00:41:44,670
(Chinese Designers: True to Vision)
new things.

877
00:41:44,670 --> 00:41:45,960
(Fresh Works, New Worlds)
So my creative spark

878
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:47,230
(Found in Creation)
comes from life.

879
00:41:47,670 --> 00:41:49,070
(In the end, as we grow,)

880
00:41:49,070 --> 00:41:50,480
(you'll learn to face it.)

881
00:41:50,710 --> 00:41:51,800
(Knowing your place.)

882
00:41:51,830 --> 00:41:52,730
A little further... Just a bit... Good.

883
00:41:52,740 --> 00:41:55,840
(Gradually understand
those deep-rooted obsessions)

884
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:58,000
(may just be a trap.)

885
00:41:59,590 --> 00:42:01,360
(When we hold kindness in our hearts)

886
00:42:01,550 --> 00:42:03,760
(and let go of
those obsessions and pain,)

887
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:05,070
(you'll understand)

888
00:42:05,510 --> 00:42:08,550
(some people are meant to be missed.)

889
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:11,190
(Those painful past experiences)

890
00:42:11,190 --> 00:42:14,150
(will only teach us to be stronger.)

891
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:17,840
(Just like learning that
falling hurts when we were young.)

892
00:42:17,900 --> 00:42:19,440
(Resignation Letter)
(Only then did we learn to walk.)

893
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:20,740
(An Miu)

894
00:42:21,030 --> 00:42:22,400
I'm going to be a journalist now.

895
00:42:23,110 --> 00:42:24,110
During this time,

896
00:42:24,110 --> 00:42:25,070
thank you for your care.

897
00:42:26,190 --> 00:42:27,360
(Many years have passed,)

898
00:42:28,030 --> 00:42:29,280
(when you look back,)

899
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,320
- (you'll sigh)
- Thanks, Professor Cheng.

900
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:33,590
- (for having loved so purely and bravely.)
- Okay.

901
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:35,630
(Look at now,)

902
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:37,710
(we'll also sigh.)

903
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:40,760
(I still hold kindness in my heart.)

904
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:43,320
(Believe in pure and brave love.)

905
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:52,480
Still wearing the watch.

906
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:56,840
Got used to it.

907
00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:02,070
Shall we grab a cup of coffee together?

908
00:43:06,710 --> 00:43:07,550
Sure.

909
00:43:18,670 --> 00:43:19,510
I'm here.

910
00:43:20,880 --> 00:43:22,150
Let's go. The movie is starting.

911
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:23,800
Hey, hey.

912
00:43:23,800 --> 00:43:25,420
(Cinema)

913
00:43:26,510 --> 00:43:28,920
Why can't you be more

914
00:43:29,190 --> 00:43:30,320
clingy like other girls?

915
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:33,360
Why should I be like others?

916
00:43:33,710 --> 00:43:35,480
I don't lack love or men.

917
00:43:36,030 --> 00:43:38,280
Why change for someone else?

918
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:40,880
Do you know what I love most about you?

919
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:43,480
Watch your words.

920
00:43:43,480 --> 00:43:44,960
You're head over heels for me.

921
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:48,000
Yes. I'm head over heels for you.

922
00:43:48,340 --> 00:43:53,260
(Cinema)

923
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,030
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

924
00:43:58,030 --> 00:43:58,880
Please rest first.

925
00:43:58,880 --> 00:43:59,720
Okay.

926
00:44:00,030 --> 00:44:00,870
Bye bye.

927
00:44:04,320 --> 00:44:05,920
Hello, I'm Xiuluo Store.

928
00:44:07,760 --> 00:44:10,030
This song was written

929
00:44:10,030 --> 00:44:11,070
about two months ago.

930
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:13,840
At that time, my life was

931
00:44:14,030 --> 00:44:15,110
at its lowest point.

932
00:44:15,960 --> 00:44:17,030
During that period,

933
00:44:18,150 --> 00:44:20,190
two of the most important people
in my life left me.

934
00:44:21,150 --> 00:44:22,400
Because of my own mistakes.

935
00:44:22,460 --> 00:44:24,030
(Singing King)

936
00:44:24,030 --> 00:44:25,840
But it's exactly because they left,

937
00:44:27,070 --> 00:44:28,630
I found the drive to write this song.

938
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:30,760
And stand on this stage today.

939
00:44:32,150 --> 00:44:33,360
So I want to thank them.

940
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:35,550
And I want to
dedicate this song to them.

941
00:44:36,550 --> 00:44:38,320
Hope they're happy every day.

942
00:44:39,550 --> 00:44:40,880
And to all of you here.

943
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:43,480
(Singing King)
Treasure everyone around you.

944
00:44:43,630 --> 00:44:44,470
Thank you.

945
00:44:46,620 --> 00:44:48,320
♪I favor love♪

946
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:50,200
♪And I reflect on it♪

947
00:44:50,320 --> 00:44:51,510
Well… sorry.

948
00:44:51,710 --> 00:44:52,710
Mind if I change my posture?

949
00:44:52,920 --> 00:44:53,760
My hand feels...

950
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:54,880
Oh, excuse me.

951
00:44:55,110 --> 00:44:55,970
Sorry.

952
00:44:56,960 --> 00:44:58,480
Sorry, is your hand alright?

953
00:44:59,070 --> 00:44:59,910
Ah.

954
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:01,840
Oh, it's fine.

955
00:45:04,550 --> 00:45:07,280
I'm the new editor. My name's Liang.

956
00:45:08,710 --> 00:45:09,760
Nice to meet you.

957
00:45:10,520 --> 00:45:14,050
♪I can't explain it♪

958
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:15,230
I'm Luanluan.

959
00:45:15,400 --> 00:45:16,860
♪Only makes it harder to bear♪

960
00:45:16,860 --> 00:45:22,110
♪What I want won't return♪

961
00:45:22,500 --> 00:45:24,060
♪Some tears♪

962
00:45:24,060 --> 00:45:26,190
♪I can't shed♪

963
00:45:26,190 --> 00:45:27,480
♪The deep sea♪

964
00:45:27,480 --> 00:45:29,050
♪Overgrown with helplessness♪

965
00:45:29,050 --> 00:45:34,990
♪Overgrown with my sorrow♪

966
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:35,880
Jiang Yifan.

967
00:45:38,190 --> 00:45:39,280
I won't run away anymore.

968
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:42,230
You're in my thoughts every moment.

969
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:45,440
Even now, standing before you,

970
00:45:45,880 --> 00:45:47,230
I'm still thinking of you.

971
00:45:48,760 --> 00:45:50,400
If you're still willing to trust me,

972
00:45:51,190 --> 00:45:52,030
I hope

973
00:45:52,230 --> 00:45:54,150
we can mend the wounds between us.

974
00:45:56,320 --> 00:45:57,160
I love you.

975
00:45:59,230 --> 00:46:00,670
Just choose him, Jiang Yifan.

976
00:46:01,230 --> 00:46:02,110
Because

977
00:46:03,070 --> 00:46:04,280
I don't want to see you upset.

978
00:46:21,590 --> 00:46:22,430
That's wonderful.

979
00:46:22,590 --> 00:46:24,070
I knew you'd come back.

980
00:46:24,800 --> 00:46:25,640
I'm sorry.

981
00:46:27,480 --> 00:46:28,630
I don't love you anymore.

982
00:46:38,960 --> 00:46:40,280
Thank you for waiting so long.

983
00:46:41,280 --> 00:46:42,630
At the moment we reunited,

984
00:46:43,000 --> 00:46:44,030
I was sure

985
00:46:44,710 --> 00:46:46,030
you were the one I loved most.

986
00:46:46,590 --> 00:46:47,590
Is that true, Jiang Yifan?

987
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:50,280
I'll never let you leave me again.

988
00:46:50,800 --> 00:46:51,640
Not for a second.

989
00:47:14,150 --> 00:47:15,320
Cut!

990
00:47:16,590 --> 00:47:18,590
Hurry, bring a chair for Fu.

991
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:21,630
Ah, Mr. Gong.

992
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:23,000
What do you think of this scene?

993
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:25,480
Wait, that...

994
00:47:25,670 --> 00:47:26,550
Shou Gongyuan.

995
00:47:26,730 --> 00:47:27,590
Wait, so you think

996
00:47:27,590 --> 00:47:29,360
your script design is so advanced?

997
00:47:29,840 --> 00:47:31,550
The female lead's twist is too weird.

998
00:47:31,550 --> 00:47:32,920
Don't you see it?

999
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:33,760
No idea?

1000
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:36,280
Exactly,
Jiang Yifan's delivery is so stiff.

1001
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:37,120
It's way too scripted.

1002
00:47:37,400 --> 00:47:39,510
Yes, the lines the screenwriter wrote...

1003
00:47:39,510 --> 00:47:40,440
are not realistic.

1004
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:41,800
- Exactly.
- Way too fake.

1005
00:47:41,800 --> 00:47:43,030
Way too fake.

1006
00:47:43,030 --> 00:47:44,230
Wait, just...

1007
00:47:44,230 --> 00:47:45,440
have the girl dump both guys.

1008
00:47:45,440 --> 00:47:46,550
- That's it.
- It works.

1009
00:47:46,550 --> 00:47:48,000
- That works too.
- Okay.

1010
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:49,360
But now it's too late, it's about to...

1011
00:47:49,510 --> 00:47:51,000
- Yeah, yours works.
- Enough.

1012
00:47:51,760 --> 00:47:53,000
This is my script.

1013
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:55,280
I'll write it the way I want.

1014
00:47:55,510 --> 00:47:57,230
I just want the twist here.

1015
00:47:57,360 --> 00:47:59,070
I just want this ending!

1016
00:47:59,590 --> 00:48:00,440
Let's do another take!

1017
00:48:00,590 --> 00:48:01,710
Got it, Mr. Gong.

1018
00:48:02,070 --> 00:48:03,260
Come on, one more take.

1019
00:48:03,260 --> 00:48:04,110
Come on.

1020
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:06,280
Okay, get ready for
the official shooting.

1021
00:48:07,150 --> 00:48:08,760
Hey, touch up first.

1022
00:48:08,760 --> 00:48:10,000
Come on, touch up.

1023
00:48:11,400 --> 00:48:12,440
Come on, ready.

1024
00:48:13,070 --> 00:48:15,400
Three, two, one.

1025
00:48:16,630 --> 00:48:17,880
Action!

1026
00:48:18,850 --> 00:48:22,680
♪Maybe even the darkest night has light♪

1027
00:48:24,200 --> 00:48:27,240
♪Faintly illuminating the way forward♪

1028
00:48:29,550 --> 00:48:33,220
♪Maybe withered flowers
still have fragrance♪

1029
00:48:33,530 --> 00:48:37,340
♪Awaiting for next spring to bring hope♪

1030
00:48:38,500 --> 00:48:41,430
♪Remember your young self♪

1031
00:48:41,430 --> 00:48:44,140
♪Yearning for tomorrow and beyond♪

1032
00:48:44,140 --> 00:48:48,300
♪Bravely waiting through
the night till dawn♪

1033
00:48:49,160 --> 00:48:52,130
♪Don't forget the dreams
of your childhood♪

1034
00:48:52,130 --> 00:48:54,760
♪The wishes you once made♪

1035
00:48:54,760 --> 00:48:59,140
♪I'll always be right by your side♪

1036
00:48:59,140 --> 00:49:01,840
♪Turning into the wind, journeying afar♪

1037
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:04,580
♪Yearning for the sky♪

1038
00:49:04,580 --> 00:49:07,230
♪Becoming a streak of evening glow♪

1039
00:49:07,230 --> 00:49:09,530
♪Merging gently with the sea♪

1040
00:49:09,790 --> 00:49:12,430
♪Turning into the light
to shine through♪

1041
00:49:12,430 --> 00:49:15,190
♪Break free from the long night♪

1042
00:49:15,190 --> 00:49:17,800
♪The gaze looking at you♪

1043
00:49:17,800 --> 00:49:20,720
♪Filled with strength anew♪
